channel.title: Acording to the compiler i don't have JDK so it won't compile, but i DO have JDK
channel.description:
Yesterday i downloaded JDK 6 update 14 so i could try making the server i downloaded work.. i've been having all sorts of problems. And if it wasn't for a forum mod who reminded me to compile it (cuz i forgot) :S When it came to compiling it i got the message You don't have JDK 5.0 or 6.0 and then was told to go to a tutorial, i know i have it because i downloaded it just yesterday when i started all this server stuff.
I just have no idea why this isn't working :( All i know is it's frustrating having something that worked last time but it won't this time.
And yes i've seen this sites rules and im not asking to be "spoonfed" i just wanna know why the compiler can't see that i have JDK. >.<
